<HEADLINE>
<P>
SKY SHOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Kudos to the organizers of the 1994 World Cup Soccer championships scheduled 
for the Rose Bowl in Pasadena. But how did the planners manage to arrange it so 
that during the finale on July 17, the audience could look up and see the small 
comets hit the planet Jupiter? 
</P>
<P>
 KENNETH LLOYD LARSON 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
