<HEADLINE>
<P>
RETROACTIVE TAXES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Re "Supreme Court OKs Retroactive Tax Collection," June 14: 
</P>
<P>
 Now that the Supreme Court has ruled that retroactive taxes are 
constitutional, wouldn't it seem fair if they also ruled that citizens could 
have the same privilege with their votes for politicians who pass such taxes? 
</P>
<P>
 TED G. SHOWN 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo 
</P>
<P>
 * Now it's official, the government can lie to its citizens! 
</P>
<P>
 JAMES R. HUBER 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 
</P>
