<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; A GENTLEMAN'S GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EMILIO GARCIA-RUIZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One of soccer's more sportsmanlike traditions has continued during the 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 When a player is injured away from the ball and the referee is slow to stop 
play, his teammates will kick the ball out of bounds to force a stoppage and 
allow for medical attention. 
</P>
<P>
 When play is resumed, the team throwing the ball in tosses it to the team 
whose player was hurt. EMILIO GARCIA-RUIZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
