<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: COMPANY TOWN; CHIAT / DAY CFO TO JOIN FOX AS FINANCIAL CHIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Twentieth Century Fox said Monday that it has lured away the chief financial 
officer of advertising firm Chiat/Day to become the studio's top financial 
executive. 
</P>
<P>
 Simon T. Bax, who reports to Fox President Bill Mechanic, will become the 
studio's senior vice president and chief financial officer.He will head the 
financial operations tied to the production and distribution of Fox films, Fox 
video products and other matters. 
</P>
<P>
 * MCA Music Entertainment has promoted Paula Batson to senior vice president 
of public relations and special projects development. MCA said the move was 
part of the company's continued expansion into international markets and its 
interest in emerging technologies. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jolene Cherry, executive producer and musical supervisor for the hit 
soundtrack for "The Crow," has signed an exclusive production and consulting 
deal with Atlantic Group to develop soundtracks, tribute albums and other 
projects. 
</P>
<P>
 * Larry Stessel has been named senior vice president and general manager of 
EMI Records. 
</P>
<P>
 * Michael Zucker has been named senior vice president of creative services by 
MCA TV. 
</P>
<P>
 * Economist Arthur B. Laffer has joined the board of directors of ValueVision 
International, the Minneapolis-based home shopping channel. 
</P>
<P>
 * Adam R. Platnick is the new chief operating officer at film producer New 
Regency Productions. 
</P>
<P>
 * Fox Broadcasting has named Mark Kern vice president of corporate public 
relations and Paul Gendreal vice president of entertainment publicity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
