<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: HECK WITH E-MAIL, STICK WITH F-MAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Howard Jonas is computer-illiterate. So unabashedly so that he's gleefully 
come up with a way to help executives who receive electronic mail but can't 
deal with computers: They can have their messages automatically faxed. 
</P>
<P>
 Subscribers to his service can read their mail "the old-fashioned way -- on 
paper and not on some damn computer screen," says Jonas, who offers the service 
through his New Jersey-based telephone company, IDT. 
</P>
</TEXT>
