<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOWNTIME: BODY WATCH; DULCIMER CONCERTS A DEUX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The sweetest, most soothing sound I know is the music from a hammered 
dulcimer.Whenever I have time alone, I sit down at my instrument and enjoy 
making music for myself. It must be my own private time, though. I find it's 
only my solitary concerts that bring me real joy. Just one listener is allowed 
-- Rascal, my Shetland sheepdog. He seems to sense my peaceful happiness. He 
always curls up at my feet and dozes while I play. 
</P>
<P>
 -- CAROL BURRILL, Monrovia 
</P>
