<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV REVIEWS; 'XXX'S AND OOO'S' PURE COUNTRY CORN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS WILLMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There's a whole lotta lovin', leavin', lamentin' and line-dancin' in the TV 
movie "XXX's and OOO's," set in Nashville amid the realm of new country's new 
hunks. The romantic drama actually centers on a quartet of strong-willed 
Tennessee gals, three of whom are the hunks' ex-wives, hence the title pun. 
</P>
<P>
 Directed by Allan Arkush, who deserves better, this telefilm is clearly 
intended less as a one-shot than as a pilot, with aspirations toward setting up 
a regular nighttime soap -- a "Grand Ole Melrose," or "Belle Meade 90210," if 
you will. 
</P>
<P>
 This could make for good camp, and occasionally someone gets off a line that 
at least sounds like a halfway decent simile from a mediocre country weeper. 
But mostly everyone acts and speaks in such earnest and generic -- albeit 
accented -- tones that the setting might as well be Anytown U.S.A. 
</P>
<P>
 * "XXX's and OOO's" airs at 9 tonight on CBS (Channels 2 and 8). CHRIS WILLMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
