</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MACK REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Oxnard man faces felony drug charges after he was caught tending 56 
marijuana plants near the grounds of Camarillo State Hospital, Ventura County 
sheriff's detectives said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Luis Martin Rodriguez, 30, was being held at the Ventura County Jail on Monday 
on suspicion of cultivation of marijuana, sheriff's officials said.His bail was 
set at $20,000, and he is scheduled to be arraigned today in Ventura County 
Municipal Court. 
</P>
<P>
 A tipster told sheriff's detectives that marijuana was growing in a small 
ravine near the intersection of Lewis Road and Hueneme Road in Camarillo, 
outside the state hospital grounds, Detective Bob Garcia said. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives staked out the garden and caught Rodriguez refilling a makeshift 
drip system he had built to feed water to the plants through pinholes drilled 
into milk jugs, Garcia said. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia said he and other detectives arrested Rodriguez and confiscated the 1- 
to 3 1/2-foot-tall plants. MACK REED 
