<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; COUNTY FAMILY CARE CLINIC TO OPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Conejo Valley Family Care Center is scheduled to open next Monday in 
Thousand Oaks, the fifth satellite clinic in the county's public health system. 
</P>
<P>
 The clinic, at 223 E. Thousand Oaks Blvd., will provide medical care to anyone 
regardless of ability to pay.It is expected to focus on the needs of about 
7,000 low-income residents on Medi-Cal in the east county. 
</P>
<P>
 The 5,000-square-foot facility has 12 exam rooms. It will provide family 
services including pre- and postnatal care, immunizations, examinations and 
general medicine. 
</P>
<P>
 The county also has clinics in Simi Valley, Ventura, Oxnard and Santa Paula. 
</P>
<P>
 Dr. Chris Landon, medical director of the county's Pediatric Diagnostic Center 
in Ventura since 1989, will be the clinic's director. He will continue to work 
at the Ventura center as well, rotating between the two facilities. Six other 
doctors will share part-time duties with Landon. The clinic will be open from 9 
a.m. to 5 p.m., Monday through Friday. MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</TEXT>
