<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHIP OUT VELTHOEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city of Ventura's need for a new city manager has inspired people down 
here in Port Hueneme to do their part. We are willing to sacrifice, and do we 
have a deal for you. It could be that Port Hueneme City Manager Dick Velthoen 
is about ready to move on to bigger and better things. In any event, even if he 
isn't quite ready, people down here are. Parts of Mr. Velthoen have just 
outgrown our little town, and he really needs more room to roam, a bigger piece 
of the pie, another sheep to fleece, etc. 
</P>
<P>
 Mr. Velthoen has a particular passion (or obsession, depending on your point 
of view) for developing a fancy RV resort so as to impress his fat-cat friends. 
This has caused trouble in Port Hueneme, where the yokels don't understand that 
the "trickle down" from their wallets to City Hall is for the greater good. 
</P>
<P>
 As it happens, Ventura already has an RV resort, and it has fallen on hard 
times. So Mr. Velthoen could just apply some of the techniques he has learned 
in Port Hueneme. 
</P>
<P>
 You see, what you do is declare this resort to be an amenity rather than the 
blight that it really is. Then you can charge extra for any citizen who has a 
view of it, or who can see someone else who can see it. In Hueneme we get some 
consultant to come in and testify that this will actually increase property 
values. This makes it all legit, while having the added benefit of firing up 
the yokels at the same time. I admit I'm not real sure how it works -- no one 
does other than Dick, and that's the beauty of it. 
</P>
<P>
 In the spirit of disclosure I have to admit that Dick will cost a whole lot 
more than Mr. Baker did, but worth every extra thousand, I guarantee. Also, we 
will provide free transportation for Dick out of Hueneme. I didn't catch all 
the details, but I recall that it somehow involves a rail. 
</P>
<P>
 JOANNA SMITH 
</P>
<P>
 Port Hueneme 
</P>
