<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: VALLEY HOSTS SOUGHT FOR FOREIGN STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A program that finds homes for teen-age foreign exchange students is looking 
for host families in the San Fernando Valley area. 
</P>
<P>
 "They are here to learn how to be an American teen-ager," said Kathleen 
Keever, the California regional director for the Academic Year in American 
program, which brings 2,000 students from more than 20 countries to the United 
States each year. 
</P>
<P>
 The students are 15 to 18 years old, and spend either a school year or 
semester with their host families. 
</P>
<P>
 "By the time they leave, they feel they really have a second family," Keever 
said. "About 80 to 100 of the students are placed in California, including the 
Los Angeles area. 
</P>
<P>
 "The kids who come over here are timid and shy at first. It's a big jump for 
them to leave their home countries," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested in being a host family can call Keever at (800) 458-7100. ED 
BOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
