<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: BANKING & FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bank of the West Completes Purchase of Citibank Branches: The San 
Francisco-based unit of the French banking group Banque Nationale de Paris has 
completed its acquisition of Citibank's California unit, expanding Bank of the 
West's network in Northern California.The acquisition, whose terms were not 
disclosed, is the fourth by the unit in four years. Bank of the West's branch 
network has grown from 39 to 106 since 1990. The branch sale is part of a 
restructuring of Citibank's California operations. Last week, the Citicorp unit 
said it will sell the deposits of six San Diego County branches to Great 
Western Bank. After the restructuring, Citibank will have 89 branches in 
California. 
</P>
