agreement to acquire the die casting and finishing business of giant 
Hewlett-Packard Co. for an undisclosed sum. 
</P>
<P>
 The transaction, which would add about 40 employees to Hyatt's operations, is 
expected to be completed this fall, H-P executives said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cypress company, which makes casings and other metal parts for computers 
and other products, said it will move H-P's die casting division from its Palo 
Alto fabrication center to a new structure in San Jose. 
