<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: SYNCOR EXPECTS PROFIT TO BE LOWER THAN PROJECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Syncor International Corp., a Chatsworth provider of specialty 
pharmaceuticals, said it expects to report a profit of about $700,000 to $1 
million for its second quarter ending June 30, well below analysts' 
projections. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's net sales are expected to range from $81 million to $82 million. 
</P>
<P>
 A year earlier, Syncor earned $3.1 million from continuing operations on net 
sales of $59.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Syncor said its financial results have been hurt by lower prices it adopted 
because of competition, and its plan to increase its market penetration and 
market share with certain products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
