<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: PICO PRODUCTS REPORTS GAINS IN 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pico Products Inc., a supplier of pay-television security devices, satellite 
antennas and cable TV components, reported a $218,781 profit in its fiscal 
third quarter that ended April 30. 
</P>
<P>
 A year earlier, the Lake View Terrace company had a $362,223 loss, largely 
because of legal expenses related to two lawsuits filed by former Pico Products 
President Bernard K. Hitchcock, who was fired in 1991.Pico Products settled the 
suits last year, and its total costs of the settlement and other legal expenses 
during the year were about $850,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Pico Products' revenue in the latest quarter was $7.77 million, a 22% gain 
from the $6.36 million in revenue a year before. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months, the company had net income of $683,765, while its revenue 
rose 33%, to $22.7 million. In the same period a year earlier, it lost $441,128 
on $17.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Pico Products also said it has benefited from growing worldwide demand for 
cable TV. 
</P>
</TEXT>
