REGIONAL EARNINGS: OROAMERICA REPORTS 61% PROFIT DROP IN 1ST QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 OroAmerica Inc., a Burbank manufacturer and distributor of gold jewelry, 
reported that its profit declined 61% in its fiscal first quarter that ended 
March 29, to $650,000 from $1.65 million in net income a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's net sales rose 9% in the latest quarter, to $48.1 million from 
$44.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
 OroAmerica said the drop in earnings was primarily due to inventory accounting 
changes because of a substantial reduction in the amount of gold owned by the 
company. 
</P>
