<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: ADVANCED PHOTONIX REPORTS LOSS FOR YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Advanced Photonix Inc., a Camarillo maker of silicon photodetectors, reported 
increased losses for its fiscal fourth quarter and year ended April 3. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's fourth-quarter loss was $1.65 million, in contrast to a 
year-earlier loss of $602,000.Its revenue rose 8% in the quarter, to $1.47 
million from $1.35 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the year, Advanced Photonix lost $3.9 million, while its revenue fell 12%, 
to $6.27 million. In fiscal 1993, it lost $2.3 million on $7.16 million in 
revenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Advanced Photonix blamed the large losses on lower-than-expected sales, 
particularly to the military sector, higher research and development costs, and 
adjustments made for obsolete inventory. 
</P>
<P>
 The company also said it reduced its work force by 14% in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Photodetectors convert light into electronic energy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
