<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: HOME SALES INCREASE 10TH CONSECUTIVE MONTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Home sales in Ventura County increased for the 10th month in a row in May, 
rising 33% over the same month last year. 
</P>
<P>
 A total of 1,005 houses and condominiums changed hands last month, according 
to escrows surveyed by Dataquick Information Systems. The total includes both 
new and existing homes. 
</P>
<P>
 Prices, however, continued to fall. The median price for homes sold in the 
county last month was $183,000, down nearly 10% from May, 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Another reporting service. TRW REDI Property Data, said that in the first five 
months of this year, a total of 3,775 homes were sold in the county, up 18% 
from a year earlier. The median price through May this year was $226,280, down 
2%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
