<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SEAL BEACH; NON-EVENT TO MARK SHELTER'S 15TH YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Interval House, which operates crisis shelters for battered women and their 
children, will mark its 15th anniversary by holding a pseudo-event, the "No 
Show Dinner Dance." 
</P>
<P>
 Supporters are invited to stay home Friday rather than being subjected to 
"boring speeches," a "rubber-chicken dinner" and "an elevator-music band." 
</P>
<P>
 Donations will help Interval House provide services for domestic violence 
victims. These services include a 24-hour hot line, food and clothing 
donations, counseling, housing assistance and emergency shelter. 
</P>
<P>
 Interval House, based in Seal Beach, serves women and their children in the 
greater Orange County and Long Beach areas. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information on the non-event fund-raiser, call (310) 594-9492. The 
hot line is (714) 891-8121. ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
