<P>
COCKTAIL WAITRESS, 23, MAN FOUND SLAIN IN HER APARTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WEBER, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An unidentified man and a 23-year-old cocktail waitress were found shot to 
death on the floor of the woman's Santa Ana apartment Monday, more than six 
hours after neighbors reportedly heard the shots, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana Police Lt. Robert Helton said a resident of the apartment complex in 
the 1100 block of West Civic Center Drive apparently heard the shots at about 5 
a.m., but the apartment manager was not told until about 11:30 a.m., when she 
called police. 
</P>
<P>
 "When we entered the apartment, it was obvious to us they had been dead for 
some time," Helton said. 
</P>
<P>
 Both the woman, whose identity was being withheld until relatives could be 
notified, and the man had been shot numerous times in the chest, Helton said. 
</P>
<P>
 Helton said police have no witnesses or motives for the slayings. 
</P>
<P>
 There was no sign of forced entry nor were the woman's belongings disturbed, 
he said. 
</P>
