<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOST FAMILIES SOUGHT FOR FRENCH TEENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Host families are sought for several French teen-age students who will visit 
Orange County this summer. 
</P>
<P>
 The International Education Forum is looking for at least 13 temporary homes 
for stays of up to a month. 
</P>
<P>
 "They are between ages 14 and 18, ready to practice their English, indulge in 
some shopping and, most importantly, make a friend in America," said Lila 
Brumbeck, coordinator of the county chapter of the International Education 
Forum. 
</P>
<P>
 Families willing to host male students are especially needed, Brumbeck said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Pretty much the long-waiting students (for a host family) are boys," she 
said. "Families by far are more apt to host a girl than a boy, so despite their 
strong records in academics, sports and art, boys wait for a long time. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is true across the board for teen-agers from all countries: Brazil, 
Croatia, the Czech Republic, Denmark, Germany and other places." 
</P>
<P>
 The students speak English and have their own spending money and insurance. 
Those interested in participating in the student exchange program, call (714) 
362-0810. 
</P>
