<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: WESTLAKE VILLAGE; DOLE FOOD CO. PLANS CORPORATE COMPLEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KURT PITZER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dole Food Co. plans to build a 525,000-square-foot corporate headquarters in 
Westlake Village by the end of 1995, a project hailed by city officials as a 
welcome addition to the city's growing business center. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction of the $88-million business complex at Lindero Canyon Road west 
of Valley Oaks Memorial Park is expected to begin later this summer, with the 
first three buildings scheduled for completion by December, 1995, said Westlake 
Village Planning Director Bob Theobald. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council approved development agreements for the project earlier this 
month, with no public comment on the plan, Theobald said. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's really a first-rate plan," Theobald said. "I think it will improve the 
entire quality of the business park on that side of the freeway." 
</P>
<P>
 More than half of the project will be outdoor garden areas, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dole moved to Westlake Village from Florida in 1991, and has been leasing 
office space for about 1,000 employees, who will occupy the new corporate 
headquarters, said Tom Pernice, vice president of public affairs for the 
company. 
</P>
<P>
 "We came for the quality of life, among other things," Pernice said. "It's a 
great, well-thought-out community with good services and an excellent work 
force to draw from." 
</P>
<P>
 The construction project is the largest approved in Westlake Village in the 
last five years, Theobald said.  
</P>
<P>
 The City Council approved the 130-acre Westlake North business center on the 
other side of Lindero Canyon Road in 1989, but construction of that project has 
been on hold. KURT PITZER 
</P>
</TEXT>
