<P>
POLICE SEEKING IDENTITY OF BODY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DOUGLAS ALGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Law enforcement authorities unable to identify a woman's body found last week 
along a winding, two-lane road here have released a composite sketch of the 
woman. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman is described as Hispanic, in her 20s, 5 feet 8 inches tall and 165 
pounds, with brown eyes and curly, shoulder-length hair apparently dyed auburn, 
according to Sheriff's Deputy Larry Mead.She was found wearing a light green, 
short-sleeve knit shirt and blue jeans. 
</P>
<P>
 A passing motorist discovered the body shortly after 4 a.m. June 14 along 
Ridge Route Road in a rural area about 5 1/2 miles north of Lake Hughes Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Homicide detectives have examined the site, but no information about her 
injuries or the possible cause of death has been released. DOUGLAS ALGER 
</P>
