<HEADLINE>
<P>
FORMER TITAN QUARTERBACK ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kansas State quarterback Chad May, a transfer from Cal State Fullerton, has 
been arrested for driving under the influence in Manhattan, Kan. 
</P>
<P>
 May, 22, was arrested early Saturday after an officer observed him making an 
illegal turn, said Riley County Police Lt. Rodney Jager. 
</P>
<P>
 After the officer stopped the vehicle, he found probable cause for the DUI 
arrest. 
</P>
<P>
 May was released after posting $500 bond. 
</P>
<P>
 Coach Bill Snyder declined comment on the arrest. 
</P>
<P>
 As a junior last fall in his first season with the Wildcats, May set school 
records by passing for 2,682 yards and 16 touchdowns. He also set a Big Eight 
record by passing for 489 yards against Nebraska. He was named all-conference 
quarterback in a vote of Big Eight coaches. 
</P>
<P>
 May was Fullerton's starting quarterback in 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
