<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: CORFU; EU SEEKS PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Leaders of the 12 European Union nations convene on this Greek island Thursday 
and Friday to choose a successor to Jacques Delors as president of the EU's 
powerful executive commission.There is already talk of a possible deadlock at 
the meeting, the EU's semiannual summit. 
</P>
<P>
 Delors' second five-year term expires at the end of the year, so if no 
successor is chosen at Corfu a special summit may be required in the fall. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, Russian President Boris N. Yeltsin will come to Corfu to sign a 
trade agreement with the European Union. The accord is considered an important 
link binding Russia with the West. 
</P>
</TEXT>
